The paper discusses the development of an autonomous micro aerial vehicle (MAV) for indoor scenarios, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for navigation and stabilization. The incorporation of additional sensors and electronics for autonomous navigation suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the cost-efficient design and use of off-the-shelf components may also involve machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for optimization and decision-making.
